climbs.name: Unk compression route
climbs.fa: Joe -dont know his last name- my room mate

content.description: sit start way scrunched. make a hard move or two and your home free. more information to come
strait up the more chossey wall, ends in toilet bowl
sit start in dihedral, hands in vertical crack. Feet off the the right help. Make your way up and left on the blocky features.

sit start on a decent left slanting hold. Use slopey hands and bad feet on the rail to gain a good side pull. Hike your feet up and make a very desperate reach high and right. Once you get this hold its over.

 A very large wing span allows you to skip the very cool crux moves.
content.protection: 2 pads to protect the rock in the landing. Some what reminiscent of top out problem but not nearly as bad.

content.description:
sit start hands on the crescent shaped crimp with scrunched feet, maybe even a heel. Work your way right and establish your self standing on the large sloper. From here get the next sloper and either elegantly mantle up or flail your legs until you find your self on top 

 Easier stand start is possible
content.location: far right side of the wall.

content.description: start on jug rail and make some odd moves to stand on said rail. Slope your way to the top.  Only use the hold on this distinct face.
content.location: to the left of the egg protrusion, on the detached block

content.description: Start in the middle of the wall grabbing low and lay backing on the crack. Mantle onto the jug rail above you and move to the left to finish out on obvious large holds. If you stay right and go straight up from the jug rail it is hard and has yet to be done. Don't Grab the detached block as it sounds very hollow.
content.location: Middle of the wall next to the compression problem. Look for the obvious crack, jug rail, and detached block.

content.description: A classic Duluth crag (small cliff band), but with high quality rock. Quite a few fun climbs ranging from v0 to v4.
